Quote:  It became common in colonial times for New Zealand to be designated the <i>Britain of the South</i> (or <i>Great Britain of the Southern Hemisphere</i> or <i>South Seas</i>, etc.). Analogous formations with more idyllic reference include <i>Eden of the Southern Sea</i> and <i>Wonderland of the Pacific</i>.
